#    f. Run the Docker container, passing S3 credentials via environment variables:
#       `docker run -d -p 5000:5000 -e S3_BUCKET_NAME=your-screenshot-bucket -e AWS_REGION=your-aws-region screenshot-service`
#       (The EC2 instance's IAM role will provide AWS credentials automatically, so you don't need to pass `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID` and `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY` directly to the container if using an IAM role).

# 4. Accessing the Service:
#    Open your web browser and navigate to `http://<EC2_Public_IP>:5000` to access the basic web UI.
